{"type":"message","id":"e249254e","parentId":"56068140","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:17:43.841Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the config file. I need to set the Minimax API key. The auth profile for minimax is already configured as `minimax:global` with mode `api_key`. I need to set the actual API key.\n\nLooking at the config, I see:\n```json\n\"auth\": {\n  \"profiles\": {\n    \"google:default\": {...},\n    \"minimax:global\": {\n      \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n      \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe model config under `models.providers.minimax` has the baseUrl and other settings, but doesn't have the apiKey directly. The auth profile is separate.\n\nI should use `openclaw config set` to set the minimax api key. Let me check how auth profiles work - it seems like the key might need to go somewhere specific.\n\nActually, looking at the structure, I think the API key for minimax needs to be set in the auth profile or as a secret. Let me check if there's a secrets section or if I should set it directly.\n\nActually, I think I need to use `--ref-provider` and `--ref-source` approach like the docs mention, or I can try setting it directly. Let me check what the proper path would be.\n\nLooking at the config structure more carefully - the `auth.profiles.minimax:global` has provider and mode but no actual key storage location visible. The key might need to be set as an api_key directly in the auth profile or in a secrets section.\n\nLet me try setting it with the standard config path. I'll use:\n`openclaw config set auth.profiles.minimax:global.apiKey <token>`\n\nOr maybe the key goes into the providers.minimax config directly. Let me try a direct approach.\n","thinkingSignature":"1fbd74f0d1509f2fcdea5dbd83d9e2f3cf45416146492c8433036c1240719c19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1jm45or3p2fu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config set auth.profiles.minimax:global.apiKey \"sk-cp-s