{"type":"message","id":"d302802f","parentId":"0b069977","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:18:19.119Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Minimax provider doesn't have an apiKey field in the config. Let me check the auth.profiles section more carefully. The auth.profiles.minimax:global is defined but it seems like it doesn't have a way to set the apiKey directly through config.\n\nLooking at the schema output, I see `\"apiKey\"` exists in the models.providers section under various nested contexts. Let me check if the auth profile for minimax can have an apiKey set.\n\nActually, looking at the auth section:\n```json\n\"auth\": {\n    \"profiles\": {\n      \"google:default\": {\n        \"provider\": \"google\",\n        \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n      },\n      \"minimax:global\": {\n        \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n        \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n```\n\nThese auth profiles don't have apiKey values. The Minimax plugin likely uses the API key from somewhere else. Let me check if there's a way to set it through the plugin config or through environment variable.\n\nLet me look for MINIMAX_API_KEY or similar env handling.\n","thinkingSignature":"5907c56588cf5f61b0eb0a6733d5768b69933a7b91669af83cfef50ad3de47b6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qupzaikp1hjh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get plugins.entries.minimax"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":250,"output":256,"cacheRead":24576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25082,"cost":{"input":0.000075,"output":0.0003072,"cacheRead":0.0014745599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0018567599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778577477860,"responseId":"06522346c1e75f1c55abb6dc5e7c1f05"}}
