{"type":"message","id":"54154b7f","parentId":"bea16e47","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:18:33.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The minimax plugin is enabled but has no config. The minimax API key must be set somewhere else. Let me check if it's in an environment variable or in the auth profiles section differently.\n\nLooking at the config, I see `auth.profiles.minimax:global` - but I got an error when trying to set apiKey on it. Let me look at what auth profiles look like more carefully. Maybe the structure is different.\n","thinkingSignature":"f34fb249b0b9db3499eca6c8292395699a38672c3212ef7e20cdcd86ecc7fbc9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w7p5o1a0ymrf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get auth"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114,"output":117,"cacheRead":24768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24999,"cost":{"input":0.0000342,"output":0.0001404,"cacheRead":0.0014860799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016606799999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778577500162,"responseId":"0652235d7bbdca10115afcefa4bfe753"}}
