{"type":"message","id":"c44f0554","parentId":"ebf09057","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:18:50.419Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auth profile `minimax:global` has `provider: \"minimax\"` and `mode: \"api_key\"`. There's no `apiKey` stored there. The models provider has `authHeader: true` but no `apiKey` either.\n\nLet me look at what the `auth.profiles` schema actually expects. From the schema output earlier, I saw:\n- `auth.profiles` → title \"Auth Profiles\" with description \"Named auth profiles (provider + mode + optional email).\"\n\nSo `auth.profiles.{id}` is just `provider + mode (+ optional email)`. There's no `apiKey` there.\n\n\nThe `models.providers.minimax` has the `apiKey` property for the provider-level credential, but the actual API key value isn't showing up in the configuration. I need to figure out where this key should be set or if it's missing from the current setup.\n\nLet me check if there's an environment variable or another configuration source providing this API key, since the config currently has `authHeader: true` set but no explicit `apiKey` visible.\n","thinkingSignature":"6fdd8f9c232a2a1f5bc572c3f23bbeae8919c235fc561f8590c43fe7a5f8fa22"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8sfhsadioj0k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw models --help"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":149,"output":252,"cacheRead":24832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25233,"cost":{"input":0.000044699999999999996,"output":0.0003024,"cacheRead":0.0014899199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0018370199999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778577514166,"responseId":"0652236a5f8d555e6e485e36086cca06"}}
{"type":"message","id":"08a1b75a","parentId":"c44f0554","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:18:52.126Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8sfhsadioj0k_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.4 (325df3e) — I speak fluent bash, mild sarcasm, and aggressive tab-completion energy.\n\nUsage: openclaw models [options] [command]\n\nModel discovery, scanning, and configuration\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>     Agent id to inspect (overrides\n                   OPENCLAW_AGENT_DIR/PI_CODING_AGENT_DIR)\n  -h, --help       Display help for command\n  --status-json    Output JSON (alias for `models status --json`) (default:\n                   false)\n  --status-plain   Plain output (alias for `models status --plain`) (default:\n                   false)\n\nCommands:\n  aliases          Manage model aliases\n  auth             Manage model auth profiles\n  fallbacks        Manage model fallback list\n  image-fallbacks  Manage image model fallback list\n  list             List models (configured by default)\n  scan             Scan OpenRouter free models for tools + images\n  set              Set the default model\n  set-image        Set the image model\n  status           Show configured model state\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/models"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1685,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.4 (325df3e) — I speak fluent bash, mild sarcasm, and aggressive tab-completion energy.\n\nUsage: openclaw models [options] [command]\n\nModel discovery, scanning, and configuration\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>     Agent id to inspect (overrides\n                   OPENCLAW_AGENT_DIR/PI_CODING_AGENT_DIR)\n  -h, --help       Display help for command\n  --status-json    Output JSON (alias for `models status --json`) (default:\n                   false)\n  --status-plain   Plain output (alias for `models status --plain`) (default:\n                   false)\n\nCommands:\n  aliases          Manage model aliases\n  auth             Manage model auth profiles\n  fallbacks        Manage model fallback list\n  image-fallbacks  Manage image model fallback list\n  list             List models (configured by default)\n  scan             Scan OpenRouter free models for tools + images\n  set              Set the default model\n  set-image        Set the image model\n  status           Show configured model state\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/models","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778577532126}}
