{"type":"message","id":"9815e45a","parentId":"74c9ef8a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:19:36.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auth profile only has `provider` and `mode` - no `apiKey`. I need to find how to set the apiKey. Let me try with the `openclaw config set` command but with the right path. Maybe I need to set it differently - perhaps using `secrets` or environment variable approach.\n\nLooking at the config structure, `auth.profiles.minimax:global` takes `provider` and `mode` but there's no `apiKey` field there. The model provider's apiKey is set in `models.providers.minimax.apiKey`. But there is no apiKey in the models provider config shown.\n\nThe Minimax plugin (`plugins.entries.minimax`) also doesn't have the apiKey. \n\nI'm seeing the apiKey might be stored in the plugin configuration under `plugins.entries.minimax.config`, but I need to verify the actual Minimax plugin schema to confirm where this value should live. Let me check what fields are actually available in that section.\n\nLooking at the auth profile structure, I'm noticing the apiKey field is missing from `auth.profiles.minimax:global` even though the schema shows it should be there. I should try setting it directly with the config set command to see if that works, or explore whether the apiKey needs to be provided through a different mechanism like environment variables or secrets management.\n\nLooking at the error more carefully - \"Unrecognized key: apiKey\" suggests the schema validation is rejecting this field at this particular path. This could mean the auth profile schema doesn't actually support apiKey at this level, or there's a different structure I need to use. Let me examine the actual Minimax provider configuration to understand where apiKey should actually be placed.\n","thinkingSignature":"3aa8ac86f364e1f7ffbb009e3607b8218b2055b8b517ac989d52fac2c7557c07"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tk4ja8bg107_1","name":"exec","argument